quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,73,"We have made it a reminder{1} and provision for the travelers,{2}",footnotes:1:Of the great fire of Hell.In the form of flints or other means by which to ignite fire.  Travelers are mentioned because of the special convenience to them, although it is a provision for all people in general.
  56,74,"So exalt the name of your Lord, the Most Great."
  56,75,"Then I swear by the setting of the stars,{1}",footnotes:1:Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) confirms absolutely by oath.
  67,13,"And conceal your speech or publicize it; indeed, He is Knowing of that within the breasts."
  67,14,"Does He who created not know,{1} while He is the Subtle, the Aware?",footnotes:1:Another accepted meaning is "Does He not know those whom He created...?"
  67,15,"It is He who made the earth tame{1} for you - so walk among its slopes and eat of His provision - and to Him is the resurrection.",footnotes:1:i.e., stable and subservient.
  68,7,"Indeed, your Lord is most knowing of who has gone astray from His way, and He is most knowing of the [rightly] guided."
  68,8,"Then do not obey the deniers."
  68,9,"They wish that you would soften [in your position], so they would soften [toward you]."
  69,4,"Thamūd and ʿAad denied the Striking Calamity [i.e., the Resurrection]."
  69,5,"So as for Thamūd, they were destroyed by the overpowering [blast]."
  69,6,"And as for ʿAad, they were destroyed by a screaming,{1} violent wind",footnotes:1:Or "cold."